transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you so much for calling Viagra. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: My name is Richard Steiner and I actually signed up for that Score Blue account back in October.

Speaker 1: I got it in November. I cancelled it in December and then I see they charged my account in January again.

Speaker 2: Okay, I can pull up your account here but I think I know what happened.

Speaker 1: Due to HIPAA laws you are required to just call and confirm your date of birth and identity.

Speaker 2: But we can do that right now.

Speaker 1: I did that in December. I thought they actually sent me a form.

Speaker 2: You called?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Let me double check here. Could I just get your full name and date of birth?

Speaker 1: My name is Richard Steiner, July 9, 1962.

Speaker 2: On my end I do see you sent an email request but then they should have replied back with the requirement to call.

Speaker 1: But we can take care of this now.

Speaker 2: I actually had an email that said you're all set because I asked her so I don't have to do anything more.

Speaker 1: But I did call too.

Speaker 2: Interesting.

Speaker 1: So this prescription was for the 50 mg Viagra AGV, correct?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: So when you signed up, you did sign up during a promotional period, Richard.

Speaker 2: You're actually not required or obligated to get this monthly.

Speaker 1: If you wanted to continue access to the prescription you could just simply pause it.

Speaker 2: And that would allow you to call in and place orders as needed.

Speaker 1: No, I don't want it anymore.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Well, I can go ahead and cancel this for you.

Speaker 2: So upon cancellation this prescription is officially closed.

Speaker 1: Any future prescriptions would require a new health survey, consultation and approval by doctor.

Speaker 2: Do you accept those terms?

Speaker 1: That's fine.

Speaker 2: But I'm still going to be charged for January's?

Speaker 1: Well, sir, that has already been shipped.

Speaker 2: If you want, you can return that for a refund.

Speaker 1: So I've got to pay for shipping?

Speaker 2: That's what you're saying.

Speaker 1: You don't.

Speaker 2: No, sir.

Speaker 1: You just simply put return to sender on that package.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Because I haven't received it yet.

Speaker 2: It just looks like the order was placed on the 24th and it was shipped out yesterday.

Speaker 1: So you should get a tracking number here soon.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Have a good day.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
